Dear Alderperson <%= @name %>,

Chicago's street sweeping season officially begins on Wednesday, April 1. Unfortunately, the City of Chicago has delayed the release of the 2026 street sweeping zone data (https://data.cityofchicago.org/stories/s/Delayed-Street-Sweeping-Zones-Dataset-3-31-2026/fuz6-n5nj/) that <%= ENV["SITE_NAME"] %> relies upon in order to send street sweeping alerts to subscribers.

Until the City publishes this data, we will not be able to send alerts to residents of Ward <%= @ward %> (or any other ward) who have subscribed to our service.

We wanted to let your office know in case constituents reach out about street sweeping schedules. In the meantime, residents can check the Department of Streets and Sanitation page (https://www.chicago.gov/city/en/depts/streets/provdrs/streets_san/svcs/street_sweeping2026.html) for upcoming sweeps in their area.

We will send a follow-up once the data is available and alerts are up and running.

Please note that <%= ENV["SITE_NAME"] %> is not affiliated with the City of Chicago.

Best regards,
<%= ENV["SITE_NAME"] %>
